extends course-layout.pug

block content
  section.jumbotron.text-center
    .container
      h1.jumbotron-heading #{ title }
      p.lead.text-muted
        | Start with the basics - the fundamentals of physics that all students of physics start with. Based on an average high school curriculum.
        br
        a(href="/courses") See all courses.
  .album.py-5.bg-light
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-4
          .card.mb-4.box-shadow
            .card-body
              h3 Motion in One Dimension
              p.card-text
                | To learn how objects move through space, we need to start with the simplest case: motion in one dimenion.
              .d-flex.justify-content-between.align-items-center
                .btn-group
                  button.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-secondary(type='button', onclick="location.href = '/motion-in-one-dimension#!/position';") Start
                //- small.text-muted 9 mins
        .col-md-4
          .card.mb-4.box-shadow
            .card-body
              h3 Motion in Two Dimensions
              p.card-text
                | With our understanding of motion in one dimension, we explore motion in two dimensions.
              .d-flex.justify-content-between.align-items-center
                .btn-group
                  button.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-secondary(type='button', onclick="location.href = '/motion-in-two-dimensions#!/two-dimensional-position';") Start
                //- small.text-muted 9 mins
        .col-md-4
          .card.mb-4.box-shadow
            .card-body
              h3 Forces and the Laws of Motion
              p.card-text
                | The phenomena and laws that affect the motion of objects through space, and how to predict motion.
              .d-flex.justify-content-between.align-items-center
                .btn-group
                  button.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-secondary(type='button', onclick="location.href = '/forces-and-the-laws-of-motion#!/the-laws-of-motion';") Start
                //- small.text-muted 9 mins
